      <h2>About</h2>
      <p>This project was built in 2 days by three enthusiastic developers</p>
      <p>The aim is to encourage companies to provide a measured approach to their mission statements. These statements will then be independently assessed (by an appropriate individual) who will provide a brief proof of the company's intentions.</p>
      <p>This service will also provide these brief mission statements, proofs and some associated news stories to the public in 3 formats:</p> 
      <ul>
        <li>A JSON api allowing developers/ data analysts to collate and explore the data more thoroughly</li>
        <li>A Windows App that provides a smooth clean interface to explore the data on a variety of devices.</li>
        <li>A responsive web site that allows for quick exploration of the companiesi ncluded</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section>
    <div class="wrapper">
      <h2>Technical Stuff</h2>
      <p>The project is made of three parts, each work together to provide the end user with easy access to companies, their mission statements and news stories about them.
      </p>
      
      <h3>Part 1: Windows Store Client</h3>
      <p>Kaelan has written a C# windows application that can retried data about companies using a JSON search api, as well as create a company and post it to the service.</p>
      
      <h3>Part 2: Ruby Web Client/Service</h3>
      <p>Anders wrote a ruby servicet hat provides information on a company in json format as well as in a human readable html format. All Data is stored in a database connected to the ruby app. On creation of a new company via the windows client or the html forms a request for news stories is passed to the news sentiment service.
      Each company has its core data created in two processes, one for the company</p>

      <h3>Part 3: News Sentiment Analysis Service</h3>
      <p>Craig spent time writing a service that retrieves new sources based on the company name, analyses them for their sentiment then posts them to the Ruby Web client for storage in relation to a specific company.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
